# Quick Start

## 1. Scaffold & install

```bash
uvx copier copy gh:Cognitivemesh/pyarnes {{ project_module }}
cd {{ project_module }}
uv sync                  # runtime deps + pyarnes-* into [dependency-groups.dev]
uv run tasks check       # lint + typecheck + test
```

`src/{{ project_module }}/` is plain Python — it doesn't import pyarnes.
Pyarnes packages live in the dev group and power `.claude/hooks/`,
`.claude/agent_kit/`, the `tasks` CLI, and `tests/bench/`.
{% if adopter_shape != "blank" %}
## 2. Try the shape example

```bash
uv run scripts/examples/{{ adopter_shape }}/<name>.py   # ls scripts/examples/{{ adopter_shape }}/ to discover
```

Each example is a **PEP 723** script. The `# /// script ... # ///` header
declares exactly the deps it needs (kreuzberg, boto3, httpx + pydantic, …);
`uv run` resolves them into an isolated cached env without touching your
project venv.

These scripts are **illustrative only** — when you're ready to integrate a
library into your app, add it to `[project.dependencies]` and port the
logic into `src/` or `.claude/agent_kit/tools/`.
{% endif %}
## 3. Write your first test

This project starts with no `tests/` directory. When you're ready, ask Claude Code:

> "Write a test for my `Greeter` class"

The bundled **python-test skill** scaffolds the `tests/` tree and your
first test file, following pyarnes TDD conventions (async-first,
Red → Green → Refactor). Then:

```bash
uv run tasks test        # now runs something
uv run tasks watch       # TDD watch mode
```

## 4. Add agent features

When you need an agent loop, tool handlers, or custom guardrails, look at
`.claude/agent_kit/`:

- `pipeline.py` — reference `AgentLoop` builder
- `guardrails.py` — example `Guardrail` subclasses
- `tools/` — example `ToolHandler` subclasses

These reference templates import from `pyarnes_harness` / `pyarnes_core` /
`pyarnes_guardrails` (resolved via the dev group). Your AI coding agent
adapts them when you ask "add a custom guardrail" or "wire up a new tool".
See the full [pyarnes docs](https://github.com/Cognitivemesh/pyarnes) for
`ModelClient` patterns, guardrails, and JSONL tool-call logging (relevant
when building agent scaffolding under `.claude/agent_kit/`, not for `src/`
code).
